==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Felis
<hw>Fe"lis</hw> <pr>(f⟦emac⟧"l⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., cat.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of mostly small
carnivorous mammals, including the domestic cat, puma, ocelot, and
margay, which share the inability to roar due to bone structure in the
larynx. The lion, tiger, and other large roaring cats were once included
in <gen>Felis</gen> but are now assigned to the genus
<gen>Panthera</gen>. The lynx (<spn>Felis lynx</spn>) is also called
<spn>Lynx lynx</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fell</ent>⟦br⟧
